cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about a convolutional neural network (CNN) for offline handwritten Chinese character recognition (HCCR) and visualization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the architecture of the CNN and its performance, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper introduces a modification of global weighted average pooling (GWAP), which is a technique used in deep learning, indicating that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on a dataset, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
